c:property.c:documentation:

               The fixed length of the domain that the axis will show (applies to numeric axes).

               A string value is converted to a number.

               The value may be bigger or smaller than the actual
               length of the data.

               This property takes precedence over the property originIsZero, if specified either with 
               fixedMin, fixedMax or domainAlign.

               This property can be specified with several options to define the initial domain, so 
               that its length corresponds to the defined fixedLength. They take the following precedence order : 



fixedMin - The fixed minimum is set and a fixed maximum is calculated: max = min + fixedLength; 

fixedMax - The fixed maximum is set and a fixed minimum is calculated: min = max - fixedLength; 

domainAlign - At most one fixed limit is implied by the alignment, and the remaining's calculated:

domainAlign = 'min' - A fixed minimum is set, and a floating maximum is calculated: max = min + fixedLength;  

domainAlign = 'max' - A fixed maximum is set, and a floating minimum is calculated: min = max - fixedLength;  

domainAlign = 'center' - Both limits are floating, and are calculated as follows: 

 min = center - fixedLength /2 ;  

 max = center + fixedLength /2 ;  
                           where center is calculated from the original domain : center = (max - min) / 2;





               See related axis options:
               ,
               ,

An imposed ratio value that defines the proportion between a domain interval and a range interval.
This property can be defined as a number or a string.
Ex: The desired correspondence is that 100 pixels (range) represent 25 days (domain).
The option can be specified as any of the following:
ratio = '100/25d'; or
ratio = '100/216e7' ( '25d' = 216e7 milliseconds ); or
ratio = 4.63e-8;
The ratio property changes the visible domain when a given range is defined, so the proportion is satisfied. It uses domain alignment (relative to the domain after the fixed limits have been imposed) to change the domain accordingly:
domainAlign = 'min' - The minimum is kept, and a new maximum is calculated: max = min + range/ratio;
domainAlign = 'max' - The maximum is kept, and a new minimum is calculated: min = max - range/ratio;
domainAlign = 'center' - Both limits are calculated as follows:
min = center - range/ratio /2 ;
max = center + range/ratio /2 ; where center is calculated from the original domain : center = (max - min) / 2;
This property takes precedence over the properties fixedMin, fixedLength, fixedMax, originIsZero and preserveRatio.
See related: , , ,


               Indicates if the initial proportion between the domain and range should be preserved between renders. See 

               The ratio value to be used when preserveRatio is set is one of the following, by order of priority:


A previously existing stored ratio; 

A ratio calculated from a specified fixedLength -  - and domainAlign - ; 

A ratio calculated from the given domain and range lengths; 



               When using a sliding window for real time applications, the ratio preservation allows a stable visualization, regardless of the data values provided.

               See .


Default 
                   If no related option is specified : false
                   If a sliding window exists : true
